ce:section.ce:para:
The textural properties of the pristine TiO2 and titanate-based materials were demonstrated in Table 1
                        . As a result of the formation of composite structures, titanate-based materials exhibited substantially higher surface area values than those of the pristine TiO2. Increasing the EDTA-Na2 amount would lead to a decrease in the surface area of the titanate-based materials due to the loss of porosity as a result of the presence of clusters of agglomerated particles of various sizes (to be discussed later in Fig. 7



                        ).
